[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: N, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 0, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{With a 5-card \S suit and 13 points NORTH should overcall 1\S.

SOUTH has 13 points and four \Ss. If NORTH had opened, SOUTH's hand would be good enough 
to insist on game. But since NORTH overcalled, SOUTH merely invites with a jump to 3\S.

NORTH has better than a minimum overcall so she accepts the invitation and bids 4\S.}

